Minimanimal: Minimal-Tech, Tech House and Techno DJ / Producer.

Hailing from Montreal Canada, Minimanimal (nee Carl Dionne) is picking up speed and getting a lot of interest locally. Although his minimal moniker suggests touchy-feely minimal, don't let this fool you. He's in it to win it. His arsenal of rhythms spans the gamut from minimal-tech to tech house with a big dose of techno. 

Having spun for the sheer pleasure for many years, he finally decided in 2005 to face his fears and throw himself whole-heartedly into Montreal's underground movement. In the past few years he's been making his rounds and has held residencies at many of the city's clubs and lounges such as: Salon Daomé, Stereobar, Circus Afterhours, Coda, Jupiter Room, Velvet Club, Pearl Club as well as numerous underground loft parties.

He is finally in the lab, after much procrastination, to complete his first release as producer. Once mastered the two tracks will be added to Soundcloud for your pleasure and your support. 2009 will hopefully see a few releases to follow.

Bookings: minimanimal@gmail.com

One SP also appears in several documentaries, soundtracks of plays and films, mixtapes, album featurings , and on New Flesh first single – international networks – kicking off the third ever release on Big Dada recordings.

In 2001 he decides to move to edinburgh in Scotland and since then he’s still the premiere French MC – and the only one ! – known to drop sick freestyles all over Edinburgh!

DJ Clivester - 44 years old from Vienna.

Growing up in New York City in the 80's his biggest influence by then was Rap and Electronic music. When he moved back to Austria, he almost immediately started working as a DJ in various Austrian clubs until in 1991 Clivester finally switched sides and worked for over 10 years for various record companies in Austria.

During this time he co-produced some records until he completely turned his back to music biz and started his own company (advertising agency). Thats what Clivester does now - but of course he couldnt resist music biz for long and so most of his current clients are in this business... The few moments Clivester has on his own, he remixes songs for friends or tries to create some fun mashups.

Musician / DJ / Producer / Engineer / UX Designer from based out of London, UK and Boston, USA.

Music is a universal language so whatever i'm feeling i'll work on. Previously been resident at some the largest Asian Underground club nights in the UK, played in Birmingham, Leicester, London, Poland, Amsterdam, India, Tunisia.

I love electronic music especially Drum & Bass, House (Deep, Tech, Electro, Minimal), Dubstep, and everything in between. I feel music recently has lost a lot of its musicality so I am try and bring that to electronic music in my own way. Lets see what happens.

Mixedmedia (Na.CL.) & iLL Omen (aka The Venture Brothers) 
(Elm Imprint, Faction Digital Recordings, Miles A.Head Recordings, Bassdrive, Mac2, Flex, Patrol The Skies, Rockers 175)

Originally hailing from Richmond VA, the duo known as The Venture Brothers (iLL Omen & Mixedmedia) have long been known in the Central VA area as two of the best dnb djs for over a decade while under the Miles A. Head Recordings camp. Together, they are a force to be reckoned with in the studio and behind the decks, utilizing the full spectrum of drum & bass to create vibrant, entertaining sets known for keeping listeners moving on the dancefloor.


 Mixedmedia - Dallas, TX
  
  
Since 1998, Mixedmedia (formerly known as Na.CL.) has been a fixture of the Central & SE Virginia Drum & Bass scene, either playing alongside regional and international talent or working in the studio to produce eclectic dancefloor killers. During his many years in Richmond VA, he was a part of Will Miles' Miles A. Head Recordings... and along with Will, Kjell, and iLL Omen...he worked on constructing his own sound under their tutelage. His sets are frequently associated heavier, dub-laden, and sometimes darker aspects of drum and bass. In the studio as 1/2 of the Venture Bros. with iLL Omen, he produces a wide variety of tunes from bootleg mashups to video-game sounding steppers to catchy rollers infused with pop culture samples that keep audiences talking and crowds moving. Now as a North Texas transplant, he brings the signature sound Richmond and Miles A. Head are known for to the Lone Star state.

iLL Omen - Richmond VA.

"I play Drum and Bass. Simple. No sub-genres – no corny categories or kitchy labels. Been working at this for many years and came up with a Dance Hall 45 in one hand and a Hip Hop 12″ in the other. (<-- There is your chance for a cheap laugh!) Selection, pressure, and mix choppage are the forte. I play cuts that I enjoy - new, old, obscure - whatever. I like to slice up breaks and bass lines on the fly and construct new bits on the fly. I'm as much of a collector as I am a DJ and aside from playing/making music, I love soul food - a.k.a. PLEASE point me in the direction of the best soul food joint in town. Shows I have played? Many. Respected DJs/Producers played along side? Hundreds. Been doing this for a long while and don't plan on quitting. Other crews and Aliases? 1/2 of the Venture Brothers, 1/3 of VA Pressure, 1/2 of the Cash Money Brothers, Style Control, NUCO. Releases on MindStorm, Pitbull, Black Reign, Miles A. Head, and Brutal Attack.
Also, check out my weekly radio show, The River City Rinse Out, Tuesdays from at 8-10 PM EST on BassDrive.com"

Rodrigo Espinoza, Ensenada B.C. México
(Pure Substance Records, Stripped Recordings, KansaK Records, Bit Records)

Born in Ensenada Baja California, México, started djing around 15 years of age but his professional career started in 1998. with a trajectory of more than 10 years in music has lead him to share stages with international artists such as : Deep Dish, Hernan Cattaneo, The Crystal Method, Sandra Collins, Markus Schulz, Lee Burrigde, Mark Farina, Tommie Sunshine, Jeniffer Cardini, James Zabiela, John Acquaviva, Chris Fortier, BT, Mazi, Kazell, Numinous, Ben Camp, Randall Jones, Anthony Pappa, Luca Ricci, Kazell, Hipp-E, DJ Garth, Android Cartel, Presslaboys, Olivier Giacomotto and with nationals like Tovar, Tini Tun, Gabriel Sordo, Karlos Elizondo, Sussie4 among others.

Rodrigo is known in his beginnings for playing the Progressive House sound which was very popular in Baja California between 2000-2005. It was one of the founders of PlurFM first radio show dedicated to the promotion of the electronic culture of the state, being one of the main sources for the promotion of events in the region, supporting promoters like Sunsound, Kimika in its beginnings, some of the main promoters who have extended more in the scene.

Appearing in the important events of the region: Ekinox, Magic Illusions, Foreign Fest, Organic, Desert, Circus, Salsipuedes, Sunset Trip, Rumo Fest, Desert Chocolate, Biotech, and in the events of Kimika (Sandra Collins, Hernan Cattaneo, James Zabiela, Lee Burridge, Deep Dish, Etc) to mention some.

Throughout his trajectory has played in several cities of the Mexican republic like the City of Mexico, Guadalajara, Querétaro, Juárez City, Chihuahua, Tijuana, Mexicali, Rosarito, Tecate, Los Cabos, internationally in Ecuador and United States.

In 2002-2005 forms part of Sunsound of the city of Mexicali, VSM of Guadalajara with Jordi Riera and Carlos Toscano, to support them in “Vinyl Science Management”, project that promotes Dj's and Live Acts. with personalities like: Austin Leeds (Bedrock Record), Martin Accorsi (Yoshitoshi Recordings), Jon Cowan (Renaissance) Bill Hamel (Sunkissed Record), Meat Katie (Kingsize Record), Pavillian & Zimbardo (Sondos Records, NRK), Innate (Baroque Records). Without pausing Rodrigo it is integrated in the roster of Area709 of Canada in 2004.

In 2007, Signs with the label Pure Substance Records (Malasia) releasing his first single track Midnight Flavours the same year signs with Bit Records México Environs EP y Down Point EP. 2008 − 2009 signs new tracks with Stripped Recodrings UK, KansaK Records Mexico and Bit Records. 

Adding a great display list of radio (Internet and FM) presentations, rodrigo has been featured guestmix in programs of prestige like: 

Proton Radio: B-Sides (Chloe Harris), Mynth Music (Randall Jones), Electrofly (Shiloh), Toes In The Sand (Deviant), Unsound Logic (Adam Nathan) 

Frisky Radio: Immersed (D-Phrag), Sensations (Federico Epis), Quimika Sessions (Federico Giust) 

Afterhours 99.1 FM (Lima-Peru), ADN Alternative (Argentina), Beatbox Radio (Argentina), Underground Sounds Radio (Los Angeles), Club246 Radio (Canada), Beat Radio en DLA (Argentina), AcidSounds (Ecuador) JustMusic FM and showcasing his 2005 promo in ITM FM.

Rodrigo knows how to create the atmosphere and maintaining the energy for his public, mixing: Tech House and Techno. 

In an era where everybody wants to be a Producer or DJ of electronic music, Rodrigo Espinoza after heading the scene by more than a decade being the main representatives of the scene, Rodrigo is a true talent stands out for being a true artist of export of class like DJ and Producer.

Representing the North West electronic music scene since the mid 1990s, Forrest Avery is a Dj with over 15 years of experience playing for audiences of all kinds. As a performer he has proven his ability to please a crowd time and time again, and is known for becoming a regularly requested act anywhere he makes an appearance. As a producer he has earned himself a spot in the crates of Djs all around the world by signing releases to some of the most respected labels in the industry. 

In between headlining events around the country as well as internationally, you will find him opening for major acts in his home town of Portland Oregon. Over the years he has shared the stage with many legendary performers including Kaskade, Rithma, Dj Heather, Miles Maeda, Diesel Boy, Phantom 45, Doc Martin, Derrick Carter, Wally Callerio, Dj Mes, Chuck Love, and Dj Swamp.
 
In addition to a demanding Dj schedule, he is currently the head of the Northwest based music label Serial Sickness, and a respected music producer. So far he has signed digital and vinyl releases to both domestic and international labels such as OM Records, Guesthouse, Flapjack, Juiced, Kinjo, Gourmand, Greenhouse, and Delicious to name only a few. 

Through his production, many years of dedication and unforgettable turntable laced high energy Dj performances that feature a variety of musical styles he has successfully established himself a global following, and Forrest Avery continues to be a name to watch in the EDM scene. 

Complete Label Affiliation list:
 OM Records, Guesthouse, Flapjack, Serial Sickness, Market House Meats, Kinjo, Bridge City, Midwest Hustle Music, Juiced, Lowercase Sounds, Southside Shuffle, Funky Love Crew, Roundhouse, Cotopaxi, Intermission LTD, Audio Indika, Bump Academy, Mimosa, Meltin Funk Records, FLC Recordings, Cabbie Hat, Delicious, Gourmand, Tasty, Greenhouse, Skeet Trax.

Anubus’ roots are firmly planted in disco, funk, soul and hip hop and has forged his niche by artfully combining these genres with various forms of electronic dance music for an unforgettable experience. Sead  has always been facinated by electronic music, even at a very young age he started dreaming of becoming a dj and producer. He first got in touch with techno music at a local youth center in Stockholm where he first fell in love with the feel of a 1200.

Teaming up with a friend they bought their first turntables and started mixing, playing at local parties, doing radio shows online and recording mixes. 

It was a good time to start producing techno music and with a buzzing scene in Stockholm at the end of the 90s it was not hard to find inspiration och people to collaborate with. 

Sead has released music on numerous labels accross the world including InLab Underground, Android Musiq,  Molacacho Records, Boogle Recording to name a few, he also ran the label Dubok Sound that released the likes of Forest People, Steve Parker, Marcus Stork etc. 

He has played numerous parties accross Europe in the past and is back after years of silence with a new label BP Underground.

Seads style of music is full of percussions with a love for old analoge synths making his sound a hybrid beetween detriot techno and tech-house.

Now living in Granada (Spain), Intelec start their musical relation at the end of 2003. Their sharp live sets are electronic exercises for dancing and mental stimulation, minimalistic sound puzzles feed by influences like techno, electro, idm... always chasing new formulas to keep developing with no specific relation with any labeled music style.Their first releases appeared inside the Miga catalogue, on the trilogy compilations "Exponencial" (miga10), "Tangencial" (miga20)," and "Integral" (miga30, on two of the most downloaded releases up to date: "Esquemático" (Miga11) and "Giro" (miga19). New tracks for other new digital platforms or labels such as Minuendo Electrónico, Homeworks Recordings or Software Records. Intelec returned with their last track for Miga on "The engine roars" (miga37), a tribute to Detroit sound.

Bio in English (Deutsch siehe unten. Ebenso: past locations/bisherige Auftrittsorte):

 Nader Music:

Under the name "Nader" (which is also his first name) Nader have been DJing for many, many years. Before that, he played in a crossover band called "Bicycle Repairman" (guitar & voice). In 1994 Nader started to spin (DJ) and in 1998 to play live electronic music. Nader produced also soundtracks for TV productions such as, among others, “Mythos Swissair” (SF TV documentary by Fritz Muri).Apart from hes own project he had various projects with other musicians such as, “Repos” (keys), “Betinsky” (voice & keys), “Smooth” (voice), and “Dunvær” (guitar). Back then he mainly used vinyl in conjunction with different effect units for my mixing. In 2003, Nader was one of the five initiators of the famous “Dachkantine” club in Zurich. Due to the club’s tremendous success, he was soon completely absorbed with no time to push ahead with my live projects. When, after three busy years, the club was shut down in 2006, he decided to pick up where he had previously left off.

February 2009 Nader marked his first international release, a remix of Daniel Boon’s “Ding Dong” on “BuyYouSellMe” Records. “Rocket Launcher Team” and some other remixes followed 2009/2010 on labels like “Empro Music” and “Muenchen”. In April 2013 followed his release “Flesh” (with Remix of Paul Brcic) on the ambitious Swiss label “Neustadtmusik”. This August (2014) he had two releases: ‘By Day’ on Neutstadtmusik 007 (with a Mihai Popoviciu Remix) and ‘Raris Poubaix’ on the swiss label ‘UHU 003’. In November 2014 he was with a remix on ‘Tanzkiosk’(EP parisienne). This April (2014) he was with a track on a double vynilalbum on ‘Neustadtmusk’ again (Hund um den Renniger Turm). His ‚Walk’ release was following this July (2015) on Warenlift Musik. In January 2016 released 'Schlummerfunk' on Aromamusic. And right now many other releases coming soon.

See also: http://www.beatport.com/artist/nader/102711

Nader as DJ:

Being a technology driving individual, Nader jumped onto the digital & 4chanel DJ movement soon, which took DJing to the next level. Traktor DJ Pro provided the optimal platform for cutting edge DJ, loop, and live performances. To listen to / download some of his colourful and flowing mixes: http://www.soundcloud.com/nader

Nader’s musical style is generally based on minimal beats, Techno, or Tech House, with some elements of Dub, Melodic or even Pop. Moods range from sweet, sexy, to dark and underground.

Since many years, he has been playing weekly all over Switzerland and at times in other European countries (e.g. Berlin (Bar 25, Katerholzig, Katerblau, Sisyphos etc..), Garbicz Festival, Fusion Festival, Kabinet der Kuriositäten, Heidelberg, Barcelona, Madrid, Ibiza, Istanbul).

Looking to the future!! So stay tuned!

P.God is an Italian Electronic music producer mainly focused on Techno. In 2010 he started running the label Prototypes.

His style combines Industrial and Dark Ambient elements with intelligent Techno drum structures. His major influencers span from Electronic music pioneers like Kraftwerk and Depeche Mode to Techno masters such as Jeff Mills and Surgeon, passing through Brian Eno’s and Angelo Badalamenti’s Ambient compositions.

He released his first works between 2010 and 2013 and his 12’’ Techno outputs “Neptune IV EP” and "Ecliptic Plane EP" on Komisch label received particularly strong support.

Mr. Messiah is the alias of Kostrov Yuri, an electronic musician and Dj, who was born on 27th of October, 1988 in St. Petersburg, Russia. 

New to the game yet far from a rookie, he brings it ruff with a touch of new and old, keeping close to the original jungle roots while maintaining a fresh new vibe for the new generation. 
He's got his own unique vibe of music, which touches bass on many of the styles of Reggae, Dub and UK Garage from new to decades ago. 

Mr. Messiah is an important figure in St. Peterburg's Breakcore & Dubstep scenes. He is also closely affiliated with the Russia's Glitch, IDM and Harcore Techno music scenes.

Muti  Music = Medicine Music.
In South African English, the word "muti" is derived from the Zulu/Xhosa word umuthi, meaning "tree," whose root is -thi. In Southern Africa, "muti" and cognates of umuthi are in widespread use in most indigenous African languages as well as in South African English and Afrikaans, which sometimes use "muti" as a slang word for medicine in general, or even as a term for 'good luck'.

Muti Music has been pushing all things bass music related since its founding by Dov1 in  2002.

"If you didn't know, Hell Yeah is the Italian label hell-bent on releasing the best modern disco(ish) you can find. Sometimes it's blissed out and Balearic, sometimes it's squelchy and down-right weird and sometimes it's the sort of elongated, tribal stuff that works dancefloors into a salacious frenzy" (Kristan J Caryl - DJ MAG January 2014)


Hell Yeah Recordings, a descendent of leading Italian dance label Mantra Vibes is an Italian-based electronic music label active since 2006. Releasing from Ferrara, Bologna, and Amsterdam and led by Marco Gallerani “peeDoo” (A&R), the label bases its philosophy on a diversity of artists and recording experiences tied together by a common vision of what defines quality progressive recording. 

With a sound as diverse as the artists it represents, Hell Yeah does not limit itself to the constraints of genre but packs a complex palette of sounds ranging from techno to minimal-nu-rave to electro-funk and tech house.  Artists as varied as Radio Slave, Santos, Umek, Oliver Koletzki, Congorock, 3iO, Crimea X and the mighty Balearic Gabba Sound System have helped establish Hell Yeah’s eclectic sound, a distinct take on party music loaded with a sonic Balearic feel good vibe that has made press around the world hail Hell Yeah as a label to watch, always

Hell Yeah aims to build upon its current reputation as a leading Italian Electronic Music play, overseeing the release of a series of progressive productions that straddle genres, defy conventions and blur barriers between listening and dance music. Stemming from Hell Yeah’s initial graphic identity formed by Neverending’s Rocco “the Boghe” Pezzella, new mind-bending web and label artworks from Italian artist Andrea Amaducci and the Berlin-based Ice Cream For Free collective promises complete visual as well as aural stimulation.

Mihalis Safras is the Greek DJ/producer sensation that has – over the course of an illustrious career – forged a name for himself as one of the most hard-working and consistently brilliant electronic artists in the world. An Ibiza DJAward-winner, Mihalis is one of the most charted tech house artist of all time on Beatport and Resident Advisor, releasing on a slew of leading labels including Relief, Hot Creations, Moon Harbour and of course his own Material imprint. A ferociously dedicated producer and vinyl-championing DJ, Mihalis is a true electronic warrior. 

Significant milestones in his career include remixing Marco Carola – one of the very few artists every to have officially done so – with his interpretation of Play It Loud hitting Beatport top spot after only a few days and going on to be one of the biggest records of 2016. More recently, Mihalis has formed a unique bond with dance music pioneer Green Velvet. To date they have collaborated on no fewer than seven records – including Discogirl, Microwave and Speak To Me – with their eight due for release late 2019. 

In addition to being a real DJs DJ – there are few other tech house artists charted as regularly by their peers as Mihalis – he’s firm fan favourite, to date having clocked up an impressive ten million streams on Spotify, and regularly packing clubs from London to Ibiza and beyond. 

Currently working on his third studio album and touring the global festival circuit at EDC, Creamfields, BPM and more, Mihalis’s will continue to pursue his love of musical creation and performance for the foreseeable future. For the sake of ravers around the world, long may his passion continue.

Embracing the punk individualist ethic wholeheartedly, Johnny Gonken creates music that is totally the product of his own wild imagination. With the fervor of an artist driven by his own need to have a unique voice in the world (and fueled by the talent to accomplish just that), Gonken churns out energetic, hooky and artistically defiant music he calls quirky electro-punk rock. It's a galvanizing sound and one that reverberates with the in-your-face rawk assault and stimulated by electronic surges.

Genius and Insanity

Deviation from the norm is frequently criticized, sometimes hated. But Gonken doesn't care. He's confident in his highly original music. He has a mark to make on the world and he's busy carving it in. His music can be seen as a reflection of the hypocrisy of the music industry. The unsigned independent who steps off the beaten path is written off as nuts. But the same wacko who makes it is praised for his forward-thinking music. There's a fine line between genius and insanity, Gonken says. That line is fame. If you're underground, people call you crazy, but if you're famous, you're regarded as a genius.
Fusion

Diversity is perhaps the defining element of Gonken's sound. His music finds roots in everything from pop punk to angry industrial and a lot in between. Eclecticism drives his creative process and he seeks to offer as colorful a musical experience as possible. Besides music, he also draws energy from humor and sci-fi cinema. His inspired askewness charges through every song, his music raw yet primitive, raving mad yet with a satirical edge.

Hip hop perked the interest of Detroit’s Craig Gonzalez to vinyl at a young age, and underground parties in the 1990s soon catalyzed a lifelong fascination with DJing. Inspired by versatility, his self-taught techniques have grown from weaving rhythmic layers into powerful, personal narratives.

His collection reflects the evolution of music that came up in Detroit across decades, including  techno, house, minimal, dub techno, and plenty of hip hop and funk. He was a part of the Detroit Bachelor DJs collective with Derek Plaslaiko, and has opened for Marco Carola at Necto, Miss Kittin at TV Lounge, and Matthew Dear at Marble Bar. His collaborative skills were heightened at Solar in Ann Arbor, where he shared a residency with Stacey Pullen, and played a four turntable tag set with Carlos Souffront in support of Craig Craig and Kenny Larkin. Paxahau has booked him countless times at both Movement and large local events—like its 20th anniversary with Richie Hawtin and John Acquaviva. 

Influenced by the Mike Huckaby’s depth and the hypnotic craft of Donato Dozzy, Gonzalez has honed his own style from a global network of like-minded artists. Family, history, and culture that surrounds electronic music have been key to his deep sensibilities, which translate seamlessly across a dance floor.

LuQas is Luke Trott from Brighton UK. Known for his unique slant on psychedelic breaks, he has consistently spurned the obvious in a quest to take his music down a deeper, more fulfilling route. His tracks have resonated through underground dancefloors worldwide, gaining him a loyal global following as well as turning the heads of major international djs.

The LuQas sound has been shaped by a melting pot of experiences throughout his love affair with electronic music. Hypnotic basslines draw influence from techno, intricate synth work inspired by psy trance, tough punchy tech-funk rhythms drive his tracks along and intense, energetic build-ups reward the listener along the way.

Originally spotted by Bristol tech-breaks label Dead Famous, LuQas cut his teeth working alongside stalwarts of the scene, remixing the likes of the Robosapiens and Kraymon as well as releasing well-received originals such as Replicant (9/10 – IDJ) and Altered States, gaining significant support and Radio 1 plays along the way. He has now found his spiritual home on Broken Robot Records alongside like-minded producers; Neurodriver, Hedflux, Bad Tango and Broken Eye. His debut for the label was a scintillating remix of Neurodriver’s ‘Snake Charmer’ and he collaborated with the high-flying Hedflux on the deliciously twisted ‘Reptoid’ (8.5/10 - DJMag), which continues to form the climax of many dj’s sets, as well as finding its way into the top 5 breaks tracks on Beatport.

Alongside producing, LuQas has promoted successful nights in the South East and is currently a resident for the infamous Brighton party crew, Slackers Convention, who are set to celebrate their 10th birthday this year. His energetic DJ sets transcend genres, with breaks, progressive psy, techno and tech funk all held together by their common theme of deep, techy and pulsating rhythms. With festival appearances at Waveform and Secret Garden Party, gigs all over the UK and international DJ visits to Russia and Croatia, LuQas continues to feed his passion for making dark, psychedelic beats and thrives on sharing the experience with like minded souls.

Over the years he has played for clubs and events including La Real, Tik, Rocamar, Loft.co, Loop and Phonotica and held residencies at Berlin, Metro and Baby's. Early 2009 saw his 'Dragged Souls EP' on My Cup of Tea gain critical acclaim and support from artists including Danny Tenaglia, 2000 and One and Loco Dice. His thoughtful blend of soulful, percussive sounds, with a deep, dubby edge soon won him more fans and he was invited to release EP's on Plastic City and Darkroom Dubs, the label of SIlicone Soul. He has also just remixed the latest single from the Scottish duo 'Hurt People, Hurt People', which is due for release in Feb '2010 on Soma records. This summer saw Jairo's remix of Nima Gorji's 'Obbatala', the first release of Climatic Sound label, win him yet more support, and helped the release go on to feature in many DJ's charts and playlists. this year will be fruitful in collaborations and publications (Darkroom dubs, Kiara,Soma rec Sincopat rec,Extended play ), which says a lot of his work.____________

Lukatoyboy is a musician, sound artist and educator from Belgrade, currently based in Berlin.

His sound art practice is based on performances dealing with networks, sound and narrative, using walkie talkies and site specific topics.
Focused on the relation of chances and structures, he creates participatory works with suggested rules, questioning exclusivity and authority of an artist.
He is currently researching alternative methods of listening, using found architecture and proposed distance as tools for discovery.

As a musician, he is mostly involved in electroacoustic improvisation (based on real-time sampling of various objects, toys, voices, and field recordings) using feedback and analogue synthesizers. Lukatoyboy also produces nanotechno and free IDM on a Game Boy.

He has performed and/or taught workshops at festivals: CTM, Unsound, TodaysArt, Communikey, Semibreve, Wasted, Moers, UH, Phonart, Uovokids, Netaudio… in countries Netherlands, Germany, Switzerland, USA, Austria, Turkey, Hungary, Croatia, Macedonia, Poland, Czech Republic, Belgium, Slovenia, Romania, Sweden, Bosnia & Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Kosovo, Portugal, Finland.

His collaborations name Sainkho Namtchylak, Svetlana Spajić, Mia Zabelka, Irena Tomažin, Peter Evans, Franz Hautzinger, Eric Thielemans, Jonas Kocher, Laurent Bruttin, Martin Brandlmayr, Johannes Frisch, Georg Wissel, Branko Džinović, Balazs Pandi, and Igor Čubrilović, among others.

Since 2010, edits Blind Tapes, a participatory and chance dedicated tape label.

He was recognized with an award for sound design for the theatre play Bartleby (2011, Mini Teater, Slovenia) at the international theatre festival Borštnikovo Srečanje.

As an educator, he led numerous workshops for kids, dealing with topics of improvisation, sound art and performative narrative in most of the European countries and several states of the USA.

He was an artist in residence at STEIM (Amsterdam), Pedra Sina (Funchal), Semibreve (Braga), Titanik Gallery, (Turku) and Hai Art (Hailuoto).

Lukatoyboy is a recipient of the “Ubiquitous Art and Sound” Open Call for works, awarded by Deutschlandradio Kultur/Klangkunst, Goethe-Institut, ICAS – International Cities for Advanced Sound, ECAS – European Cities for Advanced Sound, and CTM Festival, which sought unusual ideas for pairing the specific artistic possibilities of radio with the potentials of live performance or installation in 2013.

He is a cofounder of a residency/festival MultiMadeira.

Playing guitar since i was 13, brainwashed from rock to punk to metal to hip hop, i started to enjoy electronic music listening to some industrial bands like Test Dept, Godflesh, Nine Inch Nails in the first '90s. Suddently i got involved in the first wave of electronica, Future Sound Of London, Orb, AFX etc; after i went to my first free party/festival my mind started to become opened to many new worlds; heavy influeneced by that whole movement, i got a drum machine and started to make some electronic music attempts around '97 and my first autoproduction in '99. Realized another autoproduction in 2000/2001, mainly experimental techno stuff; finally i joined Hydrophonic Records label from Milan, run by my friend Alessandro Skeeme, and started a long and still active collaboration making some techno industrial vynils like the 'connections eps 1 and 2'. The two completely mine 12"  'Masters of legalized Confusion' (2003) and 'Obscure Fairytales' (2007) can be described like this: hard edged drumrolls, variable synth grooves, changing melodies, abstract sounds bleeping in and out. I made a split album with Mechanic Willow on Idroscalo Records, Rome, run by Antonella Pintus, called 'Niente Di Nuovo Sotto Il Sole', a couple of  punching technoid electrobreaks industrial tracks, made in "the spirit of AFX taking a holiday in Italy". While taking the SAE course in Milan i met some good friends that were starting the project of making a sound system; i joined them and the whole thing has been called Untravelled Ground. Emiliano Pilloni (PilloPlex) and me started our indie electronic label Untravelled Ground Records (UNG) in 2007 and made 3 vynils and 1 cd, producing Pilloplex (Changing Doctor ep), Synthe.Labo (Blackened Happy Sheep ep), Intiman (Drug Dealers ep) and a collaboration project of me and Enzo Sarteur called 'Iron Steel Art', all with the support of the Music Lab studio for final mixes and masterings. 
2013: 'Transitions' Lp on Hydrophonic Records: a mixture of techno and electronic infuences, divided into a vinyl Lp (more groovy/acid stuff) and a digital release (more focused on my own thought about electronic mucic).
Since 2000 i developed a particular style that is a mixture of many influences: techno, electro, breakcore, idm and clubbish stuff; i have difficulties to describe my music, anyway i shifted from tekno to more break and experimental to more downtempo techno and electronica. Nowadays i'm both into groovish and mental or more experimental stuff; as some friends of mine say, even if i make an house track it's clear that i have 'warpish electronica' roots....and anyway eclecticity is the keyword.

Paul Hazendonk and his Manual Music is one of the backbones of electronic music in the Netherlands and beyond. Max Cooper, Hernan Cattaneo, Eelke Kleijn, Matador, Robert Babicz, John Tejada, Petar Dundov, Henry Saiz and Guy J are among a list of the world’s finest producers who made it onto the prolific Dutch imprint. The kind and gentle Rotterdam native label boss has seen over 35 countries as a DJ and released music on labels such as Diynamic, Sudbeat, Poesie Musik, 3000grad, Sony/Epic and numerous other infamous labels.

Born in the suburbs of Rotterdam in the early eighties, Paul Hazendonk developed an excessive interest for music at a young age. He secured his first club gigs by the time he turned eighteen and international gigs followed shortly after. In his early twenties Paul honed and perfected his craft through residencies at various clubs including the legendary Las Palmas, Rotterdam.

In 2000, Hazendonk started working at the renowned record store Basic Beat which was in the heart of Rotterdam. It was here he released his first mix compilations and A&R’d for various labels leading to the birth of Manual Music in 2005.

In 2014 he released his long-awaited debut album ‘Adapt’ which showed his versatility as a producer. The LP included collaborations with Sian Evans of Kosheen, Alice Rose, Patchy, Noraj Cue, Olaf Stuut and spoken word wizard The Lazarusman. Five years later his second album ’Signed’ followed, a compilation of his Signature EP series accompanied by a batch of fresh remixes.

Although people like to genre-tag artists nowadays, it’s not easy to do so with Paul Hazendonk. Throughout the years of his career he has crafted his own distinctive sound. Elements of house- and techno music are blended with warm basslines and melodies but without losing sight of the dance floor.

Whether it is as a DJ, music composer or promoter, Vasily Bvoice is one of Moscow’s most active figures in the underground scene and keep on moving forward twenty years later… 
 
As a DJ, his taste for new experiences led him to unwonted parts of the planet like the Kazantip Republic, Epizode festival on the Phu Quoc Island in Vietnam or even in the jungles of Columbia — but also on a boat to Thailand as well as to the newly baked Squat ¾ venue in Moscow. 
 
Furthermore, Bvoice’s appearances on deepmix.ru, nightclubber.ro, RTS.FM — more recently Megapolis 89’5 FM Moscow for his monthly show — have also contributed to his strong musical reputation. 
 
As a music composer, Vasily Bvoice has distinguished himself alongside music mates Anrilov, Danilov and Sickdisco (other activists of Moscow’s electronic scene) on Russian labels Fox Trax (2013, 2014, 2015, 2016), Body Parts (2015), Heisenberg (2015), Raro Music (2015). 
Moreover, collaborative working has always had a dominating place in Bvoice’s musical career as illustrated by his collaborations with dOP, Pier Bucci and Hatikvah on the composition side and remix-wise with dOP, Masomenos, Barac, Bruno Pronsato.
 
Finally, it’s in May 2016 that Bvoice decides to brand his hometown Moscow a little further by launching Fellows, hosting known and recognized parties at Gazgolder, Noor Bar, Kotelnaya et cetera, inviting live act guests like Egyptian Lover, Afrika Bambaataa, Alexander Robotik among others.

Subdiffusion is the production alter-ego of Bristol based Jon Richards.

I first started writing electronic music back in 1993 - the same year I went to my first rave. Inspired by the emerging dance music scene and the breakthrough local acts that were taking the world by storm; Massive Attack, Portished, Tricky and Reprezents, I began honing my production skills. In 2000 I joined forces with Mathew Carter and Laura Pearce to form Subdiffusion as a live Drum & Bass act. After five years and some knockout gigs at underground parties, as well as sharing the stage with some of the scenes heavyweights, we went our separate ways. 

Since completing my degree in Creative Music Technology, I have been working with talented people from across the world, remixing and producing tracks for artists such as Foniqz, Vicky Flint, Nel K and Queenie Moy. 

I don’t constrict myself by sticking to one genre of music or fanatically following a ‘scene’. The only consistent thread to my work is bass – and plenty of it.
I handle label and artist relations at BeatsDigital as well as all in house promotions...
